The paper focuses on a software engineering problem of improving mutation testing, which falls under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. The approach proposed in the paper involves using deep learning techniques to learn mutation models, which involves analyzing source code changes and clustering them, which could fall under the cs.PL (Programming Languages) category. The use of deep learning also suggests a possible fit with the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also involves data mining and analysis of large datasets of bugs, which could fall under the cs.SD (Software Development) category. Finally, the use of deep learning for predicting mutants suggests a possible fit with the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category.
